
## ➕ MySQL Arithmetic Functions — Tabular Format

| Function | Description | Syntax | Example | Output |
|----------|-------------|--------|---------|--------|
| `ABS()` | Returns absolute value | `ABS(x)` | `ABS(-5)` | `5` |
| `CEIL()` | Rounds up to nearest integer | `CEIL(x)` | `CEIL(4.2)` | `5` |
| `FLOOR()` | Rounds down to nearest integer | `FLOOR(x)` | `FLOOR(4.8)` | `4` |
| `ROUND()` | Rounds to specified decimals | `ROUND(x, d)` | `ROUND(3.14159, 2)` | `3.14` |
| `MOD()` | Returns remainder | `MOD(x, y)` | `MOD(10, 3)` | `1` |
| `POWER()` | Raises to exponent | `POWER(x, y)` | `POWER(2, 3)` | `8` |
| `SQRT()` | Square root | `SQRT(x)` | `SQRT(16)` | `4` |
| `RAND()` | Random float between 0 and 1 | `RAND()` | `RAND()` | `0.726` *(varies)* |
| `SIGN()` | Returns sign of number | `SIGN(x)` | `SIGN(-5)` | `-1` |

